data.enText: to get onto a ship; to put sth onto a ship

data.chText: 我们站在突码头上目送他们登船。
data.enText: We stood on the pier and watched as they embarked.

data.chText: 他们让部队在夜里上了船。
data.enText: They embarked the troops by night.

data.chText: 从事，着手，开始（新的或艰难的事情）
data.enText: to start to do sth new or difficult
She is about to embark on a diplomatic career.

ex.chText: 在纽约，你有没有在深夜单独乘过地铁？
ex.enText: In New York, did you ever take the subway alone late at night?
I would rather take the plane.

ex.chText: 到十字路口走右边的岔道。
ex.enText: Take the right fork at the crossroads.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指乘坐某种交通工具或走某条道路。

ex.chText: 我和德雷克决定乘火车去日内瓦。
ex.enText: Drake and I decided to board a train for Geneva.

ex.chText: 我们加入到等候上船的旅客队伍中。
ex.enText: We joined the passengers waiting to board.

ex.chText: 他起得很早，以便赶上头班火车。
ex.enText: He got up very early so as to catch the first train.

ex.chText: 他突然发现时间很晚，赶不上末班公共汽车了。
ex.enText: He suddenly discovered that it was too late to catch the last bus.

ex.chText: 她正要离开办公室去赶飞往伦敦的一班飞机。
ex.enText: She was about to leave the office to catch a flight to London.

synonyms.bx: 指及时登上飞机、火车、公共汽车等。

ex.chText: 他们一早就登上了开往迈阿密的轮船。
ex.enText: Early in the morning they embarked the ship for Miami.

ex.chText: 这艘船载有旅客和货物。
ex.enText: This ship embarked passengers and cargoes.

synonyms.bx: 主要指乘船，也可指船载运旅客、货物。

ex.enText: A ticket inspector got on the train.

ex.chText: 当公共汽车到站时，一些乘客上了车。
ex.enText: When the bus came to a stop, some passengers got on.
We got on the plane at Paris.

synonyms.bx: 指上车、船、飞机等，多用于非正式文体。

data.chText: 从事，着手，开始（新的或艰难的事情）
data.enText: to start to do sth new or difficult
She is about to embark on a diplomatic career.

tr: set out on (an enterprise or subject of study)
example: she embarked upon a new career

tr: proceed somewhere despite the risk of possible dangers
example: We ventured into the world of high-tech and bought a supercomputer

value.def: If you embark on something new, difficult, or exciting, you start doing it.

example.ex: He's embarking on a new career as a writer...
example.tran: 他即将开始新的职业生涯——当一名作家。

example.ex: The government embarked on a programme of radical economic reform.
example.tran: 政府开始实施一项彻底的经济改革计划。

value.def: When someone embarks on a ship, they go on board before the start of a journey.

example.ex: They travelled to Portsmouth, where they embarked on the battle cruiser HMS Renown...
example.tran: 他们行至朴次茅斯，在那里登上了英国皇家海军“声望号”战列巡洋舰。

example.ex: Bob ordered brigade HQ to embark.
example.tran: 鲍勃命令旅指挥部登船。

example.ex: Embarkation was scheduled for just after 4 pm.
example.tran: 计划下午4点一过即登船。
